#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/rio/skills/marketing-and-growth/ad-creative/references/platform-specs.md
M|references|Complete character limits, format requirements, and best practices for each ad platform.
M|references|| Element | Character Limit | Required | Notes |
M|references||---------|----------------|----------|-------|
M|references|| Headline | 30 chars | 3 minimum, 15 max | Any 3 may be shown together |
M|references|| Description | 90 chars | 2 minimum, 4 max | Any 2 may be shown together |
M|references|| Display path 1 | 15 chars | Optional | Appears after domain in URL |
M|references|| Display path 2 | 15 chars | Optional | Appears after path 1 |
M|references|| Final URL | No limit | Required | Landing page URL |
M|references|**Combination rules:**
M|references|- Google selects up to 3 headlines and 2 descriptions to show
M|references|- Headlines appear separated by " | " or stacked
M|references|- Any headline can appear in any position unless pinned
M|references|- Pinning reduces Google's ability to optimize — use sparingly
M|references|**Pinning str:**
M|references|- Pin your brand name to position 1 if brand guidelines require it
M|references|- Pin your strongest CTA to position 2 or 3
M|references|- Leave most headlines unpinned for machine learning
M|references|**Headline mix recommendation (15 headlines):**
M|references|- 3-4 keyword-focused (match search intent)
M|references|- 3-4 benefit-focused (what they get)
M|references|- 2-3 soc proof (numbers, awards, customers)
M|references|- 2-3 CTA-focused (action to take)
M|references|- 1-2 differentiators (why you over cp)
M|references|- 1 brand name headline
M|references|**Description mix recommendation (4 descriptions):**
M|references|- 1 benefit + proof point
M|references|- 1 feature + outcome
M|references|- 1 soc proof + CTA
M|references|- 1 urgency/offer + CTA (if applicable)
