M|references|**Placement-specific notes:**
M|references|- **Feed**: All elements show; primary text most visible
M|references|- **Stories/Reels**: Primary text overlaid; keep under 72 chars
M|references|- **Right column**: Only headline visible; skip description
M|references|- **Audience Network**: Varies by publisher
M|references|**Best practices:**
M|references|- Front-load the hook in primary text (first 125 chars)
M|references|- Use line breaks for readability in longer primary text
M|references|- Emojis: test, but don't overuse — 1-2 per ad max
M|references|- Questions in primary text increase engagement
M|references|- Headline should be a clear CTA or value statement
